{"name": "git-grab", "metadata": {"name": "git-grab", "version": "0.6.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Git Helper Tool", "upload_time": 1733497203}, "documentation": ["# Git Grab\n\nGit Helper Tool used to quickly add repo's to the users system for an external source.\nWith not having to worry about were the repo is being stored.\n\nInitial Goals of the project\n\n-   Create a tool to help download git repos\n-   Repos are sorted by which site and user they belong to.\n```\ncode\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 github.com\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 Boomatang\n      \u251c\u2500\u2500 dotfiles\n      \u2514\u2500\u2500 git-grab\n```\n\n## Installation\n\nTo install grab, run this command in your terminal:\n\n`git` needs to be installed before using `git-grab`\n\n```\n$ pipx install git-grab\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Overview\n```\ngrab <url-to-repo>\ngrab -r <url-to-remote-repo>\ngrab --help\n```\n\n### Configuring\nThe environment variable `GARB_PATH` can be set to insure the default local of for storing the repos.\nAt any time the environment variable can be overridden by the `-p` flag.\n\n### Cloning a repo\nTo cloning a repo can be done using both the ssh or https routes.\nWhen cloning, the data is stored in the path defined in `GRAB_PATH`.\n```shell\ngrab <repo route>\n```\nTo override the path at run time the `-p` flag can be used.\n```shell\ngrab <repo route> -p <some/other/path>\n```\n\n### Adding remotes to repos.\nThe `-r` flag can be used to say the repo path is a remote of an existing repo.\n```shell\ngrab -r <repo route>\n```\nThis adds the `repo route` to all cloned repos in the path where the repo name matches.\nUsing the `-p` flag allows setting the path where to search for repos.\n```shell\ngrab -r <repo route> -p <some/other/path>\n```\n\n## Warning\nAll the functions are case-sensitive.\nThis can be problematic when adding remotes to existing cloned repos.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "git_grab", "documentation": ["Top-level package for grab.", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "git_grab.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "git_grab.__releases__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "git_grab.cli", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "git_grab.cli.configure_logger", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "logger", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "debug", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "git_grab.cli.create_project_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "repo", "type": {"name": "Repository", "xref": {"fqname": "git_grab.cli.Repository", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "git_grab.cli.clone", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "repo", "type": {"name": "Repository", "xref": {"fqname": "git_grab.cli.Repository", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "git_grab.cli.link_git", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": nul